b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Clockwise is best suited for engineering teams, managers, meeting heavy roles, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Reclaim AI, meanwhile, shines for Google Calendar users, managers, remote workers, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2017, Clockwise describes itself as \"AI calendar assistant that optimizes schedules for focus time and team alignment.\" Reclaim AI, established in 2019, positions itself as \"AI scheduling tool that finds the best time for tasks, habits, and meetings.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Reclaim AI** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 7.0), more features (8 vs 6), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Clockwise is a poor choice — far from it. Clockwise excels in its own right, particularly for engineering teams and managers.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value excellent smart scheduling algorithm, go with Reclaim AI. If automatically creates focus time blocks matters more to you, Clockwise is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
